# AssistanceKit вҖ“ Shared UI Components

Shared Swift Package providing reusable UI components and design tokens used
across multiple iOS app projects in the `assistance` mono-repo.

## Components

### вӯҗ Markdown Editor (Internal Product)

The Markdown module is AssistanceKit's primary "internal product" вҖ” a powerful, easy-to-use
Markdown editor designed for embedding in any app. See [Architecture Concept](docs/concepts/markdown-editor-architecture.md).

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `MarkdownEditorView` | Live Markdown editor with syntax highlighting and context-menu formatting (iOS) |
| `MarkdownDocumentView` | Read-only Obsidian-style block renderer (headings, lists, quotes, images) |
| `MarkdownText` | Inline Markdown renderer (bold, italic, code, strikethrough, links) |
| `MarkdownBlockParser` | Markdown вҶ’ structured blocks parser (pure logic, no UI deps) |
| `MarkdownSectionParser` | Split/join Markdown at `## ` headings for section editing |
| `MarkdownTextStorage` | `NSTextStorage` subclass with regex-based syntax highlighting |
| `MarkdownTheme` | Colour configuration (hex strings, Codable, Sendable, light/dark presets) |

### UI Components

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `CoverFlow` | 3D card carousel with gesture scrolling, tap, double-tap, and drag-out |
| `CoverFlowKernel` | Platform-independent logic for scroll position, hit-testing, and insertion |
| `GlassOverlayScaffold` | Full-screen glass overlay with title bar, content, and action bar |
| `ActionButton` | Glassmorphic circle button with SF Symbol |
| `ScaledButtonStyle` | Press-to-scale button style |
| `BackgroundPicture` | Full-bleed background image |
| `NeonTextStyle` | Multi-layered neon glow text/view effect |
| `AnimationDuration` | Centralized timing constants |
| `SpringPreset` | Centralized spring animation presets |

## Usage

### Adding to an Xcode Project

1. Open your project in Xcode
2. **File вҶ’ Add Package DependenciesвҖҰ**
3. Click **Add LocalвҖҰ** and navigate to `shared-ui/`
4. Select the `AssistanceKit` library and add it to your app target

### Importing

```swift
import AssistanceKit

// Markdown Editor (live editing with syntax highlighting)
MarkdownEditorView(text: $markdownText)

// Markdown Editor with custom theme
MarkdownEditorView(text: $markdownText, theme: .defaultDark, minHeight: 200)

// Markdown Document (read-only, Obsidian-style rendering)
MarkdownDocumentView(markdownText)

// Markdown Document with custom image provider
MarkdownDocumentView(markdownText, imageDataProvider: myProvider)

// Inline Markdown text
MarkdownText("**Bold** and *italic* with `code`")

// Parse Markdown into structured blocks
let blocks = MarkdownBlockParser.parse(markdownText)

// Split/join document at ## headings
var sections = MarkdownSectionParser.split(markdownText)
sections[0].body = "Updated content"
let result = MarkdownSectionParser.join(sections)

// CoverFlow
CoverFlow(items: myItems, focusedID: $selectedID, cardSize: CGSize(width: 200, height: 280), coordinateSpace: "mySpace", onSelect: { item in ... }) { item in
    MyCardView(item: item)
}

// Neon text
Text("Hello")
    .neon(.hero)

// Action button
ActionButton(systemName: "play.fill", size: 52) {
    startGame()
}

// Glass overlay
GlassOverlayScaffold(
    title: "Edit",
    cancelAction: OverlayAction(icon: "xmark", label: "Cancel") { dismiss() },
    primaryAction: OverlayAction(icon: "checkmark", label: "Save") { save() }
) {
    // content
}

// Background picture
BackgroundPicture(imageName: "background", size: screenSize)
```

